          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇰🇷 South Korea:</strong>   
          South Korea underwent a significant shock this week when President Yoon Suk Yeol declared martial law and quickly reversed that decision, citing threats to the constitutional order. This political instability in South Korea is raising <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/12/04/asia/south-korea-martial-law-north-korea-russia-china-intl-hnk/index.html" target="_Blank">concerns</a> in the United States, which relies on South Korea as a vital democratic ally, with nearly 30,000 troops stationed there. The turmoil comes at a time of heightened geopolitical tensions, as North Korea has aligned itself more closely with Russia and China. Analysts warn that this could lead to regional instability, with Pyongyang likely to exploit the situation, raising doubts about South Korea's reliability as a U.S. ally.</p>
        </mj-text>
