          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:16px !important">What is Greater Hungary?</h2>
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopolitics.world/email/images/gp-dec-6-3.jpg" alt="What is Greater Hungary?" href="https://www.geopolitics.world" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">“Greater Hungary” refers to the <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-52903721" target="_Blank">historical</a> concept of Hungary’s territorial extent before World War I, when it was part of the Austro-Hungarian Empire. This area encompassed much more land than present-day Hungary, including large portions of modern Slovakia, Romania, Serbia, Ukraine, Croatia, Slovenia, and Austria. It was defined by the borders of the Kingdom of Hungary within the Habsburg Monarchy and later the Austro-Hungarian Empire.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The idea of “Greater Hungary” holds significant symbolic and political meaning, especially for Hungarian nationalists who lament the loss of these territories under the <a href="https://www.britannica.com/event/Treaty-of-Trianon" target="_Blank">1920 Treaty of Trianon</a>. This treaty, signed after World War I, drastically reduced Hungary’s size, population, and influence, ceding two-thirds of its territory to neighboring countries.​</p>
           <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Almost 104 years later, the treaty remains a sensitive historical issue, triggering political and cultural debates within Hungary and its neighbors. Some far-right and nationalist groups advocate restoring these territories, though such claims are controversial and unrealistic. This concept is tied to Hungarian identity and often resurfaces in discussions about minority rights for ethnic Hungarians living in the countries that now govern the former territories. Victor Orban has also been seen <a href="https://theconversation.com/viktor-orbans-controversial-greater-hungary-scarf-explained-195581" target="_Blank">sporting</a> the Greater Hungary map, which has triggered tensions.​</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
